        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Macron urges Europe</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">French President Emmanuel Macron has stressed the need for Europe to strengthen its militaries in response to Trump’s new term as president. He emphasized Europe’s need to <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-h3-4-reduce-reliance" target="_blank">reduce reliance</a> on the US for security, framing Trump’s approach as a “strategic wake-up call” for the continent. Macron questions  Europe’s preparedness for a US withdrawal from the Mediterranean or a shift in military focus to the Pacific. The situation of how much Trump is willing to support Ukraine is also a subject of concern.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          The European Union has depended mainly on the US for its defense. Discussions about building its defense came about during Trump’s first term, and while it wasn’t completely realized, many NATO member countries have gone on to meet the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-h3-5-2-defense-budget" target="_blank">2% defense budget</a>.  All but three EU members are part of NATO. Macron urges robust European support for Ukraine and the importance of post-war security guarantees. European leaders are expected to discuss joint defense initiatives and increased military funding in the coming months.
</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

