          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          <strong>🇾🇪 Yemeni Houthis to limit attacks</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Yemen's Houthis announced they will limit attacks on commercial vessels to those linked to Israel, provided the Gaza ceasefire is fully implemented. This move may <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-br1-6-ease-disruptions" target="_blank">ease disruptions</a> in global trade caused by year-long Houthi attacks in the Red Sea and Gulf of Aden. The group stated it would halt operations against US and British-flagged ships unless Yemen is attacked but will continue targeting Israeli-linked ships unless all ceasefire phases are met. The Red Sea conflict raised shipping risks and costs, forcing many companies to reroute. If the truce remains effective and security improves, experts expect a gradual resumption of operations. However, as it is fragile, many question how long this ceasefire will last.</p>
        </mj-text>
