          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          <strong>🇺🇦 Ukraine calls for the return of its citizens</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Ukraine is urging its citizens in Germany to return home as the war with Russia nears its third anniversary. Deputy Prime Minister Oleksiy Chernyshov announced "<a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-br2-7-unity-hubs" target="_blank">unity hubs</a>" in Berlin and other locations to aid refugees with jobs, housing, and education. Germany has hosted 1.2 million Ukrainians, with 240,000 employed by late 2024, though most women face childcare challenges. Ukraine has a shortage of workers and needs some returnees to come back to help with reconstruction. The government promises exemptions from military service for critical-sector workers to encourage repatriation. They believe Germany's support remains crucial, balancing refugee integration and voluntary return.</p>
        </mj-text>
