          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What is WHO?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-22-3.png" alt="What is WHO?" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-f1-8-world-health-organization" target="_blank">World Health Organization</a> (WHO), established in 1948 as part of the United Nations, coordinates global health efforts and has achieved significant successes, such as eradicating smallpox and reducing polio by 99%. Over time, the WHO's mission has expanded to address diverse health issues, from infectious diseases like COVID-19 to non-communicable diseases like cancer. It includes developing health guidelines, researching, and supporting vaccination programs and essential medicines.</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">All the nations that are members of the United Nations can join the World Health Organization by <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-f1-9-accepting-its-constitution" target="_blank">accepting its constitution</a>. For non-UN members, a separate vote will be held in the World Health Assembly to decide their membership based on the majority. Territories that are not responsible for their international relations will be admitted as Associate Members if a member state applies on behalf of the territory.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">For the 2024-25 year, WHO had a total budget of $6.83 billion split between universal health coverage, health emergencies, emergency operations, and appeals, among others. <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-01-2025-f1-10-who-robust-operations" target="_blank">WHO’s robust operations</a> ensured the elimination of tropical diseases, tackled mental diseases and non-communicable diseases, and advocated actions on global health threats. The organization is headed by Dr. Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, the director general of WHO, and the decision-making is led by the executive board.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
